name: Indian Health Service, Health Management Development Program
objective: To develop and enhance management infrastructure of Federally-recognized Tribes and Tribal organizations to assume all or part of existing Indian Health Service programs, functions, services and activities.
top_agency_name: Department of Health and Human Services

authorizations.text: 25 U.S.C. § 450h (b)(1) and 25 U.S.C. § 450h(e) of the Indian Self Determination and Education Assistance Act, Public Law 93-638, as amended.

rules_regulations: 45 CFR 75, 2 CFR 200, HHS Grants Policy Statement, (Rev.) October 2024; Program Guidelines for Competitive Projects.
